<section id="biventricular-pacemaker">
  <h1>Biventricular Pacemaker</h1>
  <p>
    A biventricular pacemaker, also called a cardiac resynchronization therapy (CRT) device, uses three leads placed in:
    <ul>
      <li>1. Right atrium</li>
      <li>2. Right ventricle</li>
      <li>3. Left ventricle (via the coronary sinus vein)</li>
    </ul>
    This device helps coordinate the contraction of both ventricles, improving the heart's efficiency in patients with heart failure.
  </p>
